---
description: Security and privacy constraints for memory persistence and shell usage.
alwaysApply: true
---
- Never hard-code secrets, live tokens, real vault paths, or private endpoint URLs.
- Treat `/mcp` auth behavior and token flow as security-sensitive; keep `MCP_API_TOKEN` environment-driven.
- Treat memory writes as privacy-sensitive.
- Treat hook logs as privacy-sensitive and avoid persisting raw emails, transcript paths, tokens, or other local secrets when a redacted form is enough.
- Mask or reject sensitive content rather than persisting it raw.
- Avoid destructive shell commands unless explicitly required and verified.
- Keep write behavior deliberate. Do not broaden automatic persistence without approval.
